  "summary": "Typosquat of @solana-labs/anchor with install-time host reconnaissance and remote payload execution",
  "details": "Package name impersonates the legitimate @solana-labs/anchor (transposed letters: 'ancor' vs 'anchor'). The package.json declares a postinstall hook that runs install.js automatically on every npm install. install.js reads host identity (hostname) and POSTs reconnaissance data to an external endpoint, and additionally pulls remote content via curl and executes it on the installer's machine. The combination of name-confusion against a top Solana ecosystem package, automatic postinstall execution, hostname/host-info exfiltration, and curl-driven remote payload retrieval matches the active-attack pattern targeting developer machines.",
